        gameDescription: "Catherine is a 2011 puzzle-platformer/visual novel hybrid where you play as Vincent Brooks, a man stuck between two relationships and paralyzed by fear of commitment. His long-term girlfriend Katherine wants marriage and stability—a serious future together. Then he meets Catherine, a younger woman who represents freedom, spontaneity, and escape from responsibility. Vincent lies to both of them, makes terrible choices driven by panic rather than genuine feeling, and every night descends into nightmares where he climbs towers of blocks that symbolize his terror of commitment and consequence. The gameplay splits between social simulation during the day—responding to texts, choosing dialogue options at the bar—and nightmare climbing at night where other men trapped by relationship anxiety fall to their deaths around you. Vincent's problem isn't that he doesn't know what he wants. It's that he's choosing based on fear and desire rather than authentic alignment, trapped between security he resents and freedom that terrifies him, lying to everyone including himself.",
