        meaning: "You're unfocused in learning, planning poorly, or refusing to do practical work. Like switching jobs constantly in Final Fantasy V without mastering any, the Page of Pentacles Reversed shows scattered attention, lack of discipline in study, or unrealistic goals disconnected from practical preparation. Maybe you're jumping between interests without committing to any. Maybe you're dreaming big but not doing the foundational work. Maybe you're avoiding the boring but necessary apprenticeship phase. Maybe you're planning poorly, setting unrealistic goals without practical strategy. Maybe you're procrastinating—all study no action, or all action no planning. This card says you lack the focus and discipline the Page represents. Either commit to learning something properly, make realistic plans with practical steps, or accept that your scattered unfocused approach won't yield real results. The apprentice who won't focus never becomes the master.",
